<TITLE> Govt trying to make House ineffective: Khaleda </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 2 (bdnews24.com)  Opposition leader Khaleda Zia has alleged the treasury bench wants to render parliament dysfunctional and disrupt democracy. "The government has showed its mean mindedness by not allowing Bangladesh Television to air my speech," she said in a written statement read out to reporters at her political office in Gulshan Monday. She congratulated the army for starting operations to hunt down those linked to the Feb. 25-26 BDR mutiny. She hoped that the army would carry out their duty neutrally and there would be no influence or interference with their task. She demanded that the government searched out the missing army officials without delay. Khaleda condemned broadcast on the BTV the speeches by treasury MPs that sneered at the opposition. She also alleged that the intelligence agency and the media of a neighbouring country were carrying out a propaganda campaign to create confusion about the mutiny. "It is mysterious since like those news media the MPs in the treasury bench are speaking in the same language. People want to know if there are any links.
